VLC has updated its iOS app to version 3.1, adding several new features – including support from Google’s Chromecast device, MacRumors reported. This means that iPhone users can now stream video from VLC to a screen with a Chromecast on the same network. In addition to Chromecast support, VLC for iOS can now view 360-degree videos by moving the iPhone around. It also includes several bug fixes. The release notes for version 3.1 of VLC for iOS include: